'''Henry O'Kane''' (born 5 April 2002) is an [[Ireland national rugby league team|Ireland international]] [[rugby league]] footballer who plays as a {{rlp|sr}} forward for [[Toulouse Olympique]] in the [[Super League]]

He was previously contracted to the [[Wests Tigers]] in the [[National Rugby League]] (NRL).

==Background==
O’Kane was born in [[Sydney]], [[New South Wales, Australia]]. He is of [[Irish people|Irish]] descent. He is the son of former [[New South Wales Waratahs]] hooker [[Kevin O'Kane]].<ref>[https://www.zerotackle.com/players/henry-o-kane/ Zero Tackle profile]{{Dead link|date=November 2025 |bot=InternetArchiveBot }}</ref>

==Playing career==
O’Kane played for the [[Balmain Tigers]].<ref>[https://leagueunlimited.com/people/show/henry-okane leagueunlimited profile]</ref>

He played for the [[Western Suburbs Magpies]] and [[Newtown Jets]] in the [[2022 NSW Cup]].{{fact|date=January 2024}}

===Toulouse Olympique===
On 11 December 2025 it was reported that he had signed for [[Toulouse Olympique]] in the [[Super League]] on a 1-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|website=Love Rugby League|date=11 Dec 2025|author=Aaron Bower|title=Super League newcomers seal deal for South Sydney Rabbitohs forward|url=https://www.loverugbyleague.com/post/super-league-newcomers-seal-deal-for-south-sydney-rabbitohs-forward}}</ref>

===International career===
In 2022 O’Kane was named in the [[2021_Men's_Rugby_League_World_Cup_squads#Ireland|Ireland squad]] for the [[2021 Rugby League World Cup]].<ref>[https://www.loverugbyleague.com/post/rugby-league-world-cup-2021-squad-lists/ Full list of every squad at the Rugby League World Cup 2021]</ref>

